Label: Prize or award region
Description: An ONIX code identifying the region in which a prize or award is given. Optional and non-repeatable. A region is an area which is not a country, but which is precisely defined in geographical terms, eg Newfoundland and Labrador, Florida. If both country and region are specified, the region must be within the country. Note that US States have region codes, while US overseas territories have distinct ISO Country Codes.
Format: <dd>Variable length code, consisting of upper case letters, with or without a hyphen and further upper case letters or digits. Suggested maximum length 8 characters</dd>
